<div1 type="letter">

<opener>
<note type="editorial">[Letterhead imprint: Buffalo Bill's Wild West]</note>
<dateline>Worcester, Mass.
<date when="1908-07-07">July 7th/08</date></dateline>

<address>
<addrLine><persName key="brennan.j">Major John R. Brennan</persName></addrLine>
<addrLine>Pine Ridge Agency</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>My Dear Major&#8212;</salute>
</opener>
<p>I am sending six Indians home to day. Not but what they are good men. but four of them are not fit for duty, and two of them claim their families are sick. These men all wanted to go home so I let them go&#8212; I hope it will be satisfactory to you&#8212;</p>

<closer>
<salute>Very truly yours</salute>
<signed>W. F. Cody</signed>

</closer>


</div1>
